The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Indian team in podium finish
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: There was Indian success at the Asia Pacific Rally Championship when Team MRF Tyres German driver Armin Kremer and Fred Berssen finished second in group N (unmodified) and fourth overall in the second round of the series which concluded in Rotorua Sunday. Japans Fumio Nutahara and Satoshi Hayashi, in a Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution 7, took the overall honours despite finishing level on time with Karamjit Singh and Allen Oh, according to information received here.  Copyright 
